President Obama has nominated Irene Berger for the United States District Court for the Southern District of West Virginia and Roberto Lange for the United States District Court for the District of South Dakota. Judge Berger has served as a judge on the Circuit Court of Kanawha County, West Virginia for 15 years. She has experience working as a staff attorney for the Legal Aid Society of Charleston and as an assistant prosecuting attorney for Kanawha County. Judge Berger graduated from West Virginia University and West Virginia College of Law. Mr. Lange is a partner at Davenport, Evans, Hurwitz & Smith, LLP in Sioux Falls, South Dakota. He previously served as a law clerk to U.S. District Judge Donald J. Porter. Mr. Lange graduated from the University of South Dakota and Northwestern University School of Law. Both nominees received a unanimous well-qualified rating from the ABA.